data.title: Princess Marie — Event's Blog — UFO No More
data.text:
This weekend, Prince Joachim, Princess Marie, Count Henrik, and Countess Athena attended the Copenhagen Historic Grand Prix.

On Monday, Prince Joachim and Princess Marie attended the Salute to Bravery ceremony hosted by the Veteran Coalition International ahead of the NATO Summit in Washington D.C.

On Wednesday, Prince Joachim and Princess Marie attended a reception hosted by the Danish Embassy in Washington D.C. to mark the 175th anniversary of the Danish Constitution.

Welcome to this week’s Royal Recap where we’ll take a look at the events we weren’t able to cover fully this week!

On Wednesday, Princess Marie attended the Serving in Strength: A Health & Wellness Series – Brain & Mental Health event in her role as Honorary Board Member of Veteran Coalition International.

On Tuesday, Princess Marie attended a reception hosted by the Department for Foreign Policy of the Embassy of Denmark in the USA.

On Monday, Princess Marie visited Houston, Texas, in her role as Honorary Board Director of Veteran Coalition International.

On Tuesday, Princess Marie visited the Regional Capital Psychiatry Hospital in Glostrup as Patron of the Danish Autisme Association.

On Monday, Princess Marie visited the Mad-med-Hjertet organization in Hørsholm. The organization helps to reduce food waste by redistributing surplus food to families in need.

Earlier this week, Princess Marie visited the Medical Center Orthotics & Prosthetics facility in Silver Spring in her role as Honorary Board Director of Veteran Coalition International.

On Tuesday, Princess Marie sent a video message to the National Autism Association to mark World Autism Day.

On March 16th, Prince Joachim and Princess Marie attended the annual Gridiron dinner in Washington D.C.

In February, Princess Marie met with wounded Ukrainian soldiers who were on a trip to Washington D.C. with the Future for Ukraine Foundation.

On Monday evening, Queen Margrethe, Crown Prince Frederik, Crown Princess Mary, Prince Joachim, Princess Marie, and Princess Benedikte attended the traditional New Year Gala in Copenhagen.

On Monday, Queen Margrethe, Crown Prince Frederik, Crown Princess Mary, Prince Joachim, Princess Marie, and Count Felix attended a Christmas Day service at Aarhus Cathedral.

On Sunday, Queen Margrethe, the Crown Prince Family, Prince Joachim, Princess Marie, and their children attended a Christmas Eve service at Aarhus Cathedral.

On Friday, Princess Marie marked World AIDS Day in Copenhagen as Patron of AIDS-Fondet.

On Monday, Princess Marie attended the Society for Neuroscience conference in Washington D.C. where she visited the Danish Neuroresearch Center’s stand. The DNC is part of Aarhus University Hospital.
